  <p>C7 districts are specifically designated for large open amusement parks. In addition to the types of activities
    commonly found in amusement parks, such as ferris wheel rides and games of chance (<a target="_blank"
      href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/planning/zoning/glossary.page#use_group" class="glossary">Use Group</a> 15), C7
    districts also permit boating facilities and other large open and enclosed entertainment facilities like skating
    rinks, sports stadiums and miniature golf courses (Use Groups 12â€“14). Residential and community facility <a
      target="_blank" href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/planning/zoning/glossary.page#use" class="glossary">uses</a> are
    not permitted.</p>
  <p>The maximum floor area ratio is 2.0. Off-street parking requirements are low, but vary with the specific use.</p>
  <p>The Coney Island amusement park area is zoned C7.</p>

